<item>
            <title>[JDK-4842457] (bf spec) Clarify meaning of &quot;(optional operation)&quot;</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-4842457</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Name: rmT116609			Date: 04/03/2003&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
FULL PRODUCT VERSION :&lt;br/&gt;
java version &amp;quot;1.4.1_01&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Java(TM) 2 Runtime Environment, Standard Edition (build 1.4.1_01-b01)&lt;br/&gt;
Java HotSpot(TM) Client VM (build 1.4.1_01-b01, mixed mode)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
DESCRIPTION OF THE PROBLEM :&lt;br/&gt;
This phrase follows many methods description in the java.nio.XxxBuffer classes:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;(optional operation)&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
What does this mean? Presumably it&amp;#39;s not informing the programmer that calling the method is optional, as that&amp;#39;s true for all methods. Does it mean that the method is not coded for all platforms, and that I should not use it if&lt;br/&gt;
portability is a goal?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
STEPS TO FOLLOW TO REPRODUCE THE PROBLEM :&lt;br/&gt;
1. see the java.nio.XxxBuffer docs&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
EXPECTED VERSUS ACTUAL BEHAVIOR :&lt;br/&gt;
don&amp;#39;t know&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
REPRODUCIBILITY :&lt;br/&gt;
This bug can be reproduced always.&lt;br/&gt;
(Review ID: 181077) &lt;br/&gt;
======================================================================&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
