                            <comment id="12166563" author="mr" created="Sat, 2 Nov 0176 16:07:02 -0752"  >BT2:EVALUATION&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The methods in question are marked &amp;quot;(optional operation)&amp;quot; because they will&lt;br/&gt;
always throw an UnsupportedOperationException, in particular, an instance of&lt;br/&gt;
the subclass ReadOnlyBufferException, when invoked upon read-only buffers.&lt;br/&gt;
This is explained in the specification of java.nio.Buffer, which is the&lt;br/&gt;
superclass of all buffer classes:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Every buffer is readable, but not every buffer is writable.  The&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;mutation methods of each buffer class are specified as optional&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;operations that will throw a ReadOnlyBufferException when invoked&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;upon a read-only buffer.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We can clarify the wording in the type-specific buffer classes so that the&lt;br/&gt;
meaning of &amp;quot;(optional operation)&amp;quot; is more obvious.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
-- ###@###.### 2003/4/10</comment>
